  <thing id="fDayAdapt" name="Daylight Adaptation" description="{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Dwarf (Underdark [Northdark]), elf (Cormanthor Drow), kuo-toa (Underdark [Sloopdilmonpolop]), or orc (Chessenta, the Hordelands, the North, or Thesk),\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Unlike other members of your race, you are not dazzled or blinded by exposure to bright light or sunlight. However, spells or effects that affect all creatures regardless of race, such as a sunbeam or sunburst spell, still affect you normally.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.\n\n{b}Source Note:{/b}This appears in multiple sources.  According to the {i}Forgotten Realms&apos; Campaign Setting{/i} this is {b}{i}NOT{/i}{/b} regional feat.  Because of the nature of this feat I am NOT treating it as such for the purposes of granting it as a bonus feat for those with the qualifying regions.  This is scripted to work also with the {i}Races of Eberron{/i}.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Player&apos;s Guide to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.5 and {i}Underdark{/i}, 3.5 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="You have accustomed yourself to the painful sunlight of the surface world." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="DrowUnderD"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <usesource source="srcUndark"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fReactCoun" name="Reactive Counterspell" description="You can react quickly to counter spells cast by opponents.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Improved Initiative (PH) , Improved Counterspell.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Once per round, you can counterspell an opponent&apos;s spell even if you have not readied an action to do so.  This counterspell action takes the place of your next turn. You can&apos;t use this feat when you are flat-footed.\n\n{b}Normal:{/b} Without this feat, you must ready an action each round that you wish to use a counterspell.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Player&apos;s Guide to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.5 and {b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="You can counterspell once a round without readying an action." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="pPGtF"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Improved Counterspell required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpCount] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Improved Initative required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpInit] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fAttunGem" name="Attune Gem" description="You can magically imbue gems to hold a spell until triggered.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} arcane spellcaster level 3rd+, Craft (gemcutting) skill, Intelligence 13+\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You can store an arcane spell in a gem. You must have the spell available to cast (prepared if you must prepare spells; known otherwise) and must provide any material components or focuses the spell requires. If casting the spell would reduce your XP total, you pay the cost upon beginning the attunement in addition to the XP cost for making the attuned gem itself. Likewise, material components are consumed when you begin casting, but focuses are not. (A focus used in attuning a gem can be reused.) The caster level of the spell must be sufficient to cast the spell in question and no higher than your own caster level. A gem can only be attuned with a single spell. The gem must have a minimum value equal to 50 gp per level of the spell to be stored. The base price of an attuned gem (not including the gem&apos;s inherent value) is equal to 50 gp per spell level times the caster level. You must spend 1/25 of the base price in XP and use up raw materials costing half this base price. Attunement requires 1 hour plus the spell&apos;s normal casting time. The magic gem&apos;s market price equals its base price plus its inherent value as a gem. See the Gem Magic section in the previous chapter for the details of attuned gems and gem magic.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of  Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment><![CDATA[child[aSTR].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></comment>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun" parent="pFR" name="Magic of Faerun 3.0"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="ItemCreate"/>
    <exprreq message="At least 1 rank in either Craft: Jewelry or Craft: Gemcutting required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kCrafJewel] + #skillranks[kCrafGemc] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Must be able to cast 3rd level arcane spells."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Arcane] >= 3 + 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSplGird" name="Spell Girding" description="Your spells are particularly hardy, resisting dispel checks more readily than normal.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Any dispel checks against your spells are made with a -2 penalty.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of  Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="Your spells are harder to dispel, -2 to dispel checks made against you." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="MagFaerun" parent="pFR" name="Magic of Faerun 3.0"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSpTheme" name="Spell Thematics" description="Your spells manifest with a distinct theme or appearance.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Arcane spellcaster level 1st\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b}  Due to the unusual appearance of your spells, the DC of any Spellcraft check made to identify a spell you have cast increases by +4. In addition, you may designate one spell you know per spell level as a thematic spell and cast it at +1 caster level. As you gain access to new spell levels, you can designate new thematic spells; you don&apos;t need to select this feat again to acquire new thematic spells.\n\nNearly any theme is possible, so long as you can describe a visual link for unification. For example, your theme might be {i}&quot;lightning,&quot; &quot;spheres,&quot; or &quot; screaming skulls.&quot;{/i}  If you choose spheres as your theme, your magic missiles might take the form of glowing spheres of light, and your summoned monsters might emerge from mysterious rainbow-colored globes. If your theme is {i}&quot;lightning,&quot;{/i} your haste spell might manifest as a bright green spark that leaps from ally to ally.\n\nYou can&apos;t use this feat to make your spell manifestations invisible, nor do your spell thematics change the type of damage a spell deals, regardless of its appearance.  This feat supersedes the version found in {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n.{/i}\n\n{b}Source:{/b} &lt;{i}Player&apos;s Guide to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.5 Edition&gt; and {i}Magic of  Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>This version supercedes its 3.0 version found in Magic of Faerun.</comment>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun" parent="pFR" name="Magic of Faerun 3.0"/>
    <usesource source="pPGtF"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Metamagic"/>
    <exprreq message="Must be able to cast 3rd level arcane spells."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Arcane] >= 1 + 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSplFireWi" name="Spellfire Wielder" description="You are one of the rare people who have the innate talent to control raw magic in the form of spellfire.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} 1st level required.  Approval of the DM.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You can use spellfire to absorb spell energy, fire destructive blasts, or heal others, as described in the Spellfire section of the previous chapter.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can only take this feat as a 1st-level character. Acquiring this feat requires the approval of the DM.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of  Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Feat" summary="You are able to wield Spellfire." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="MagFaerun" parent="pFR" name="Magic of Faerun 3.0"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xSplFAbsor"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xSplFAtk"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xSplFHeal"></bootstrap>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xSplFAtk" name="Spellfire Attack" description="Spellfire Attack\n\nAs a standard action, a spellfire wielder may expend stored spellfire energy levels as a melee or ranged touch attack (maximum range of 400 ft), dealing 1d6 points of spellfire damage per level expended (Reflex half, DC 20).  Spellfire damage is half fire damage and half raw magical power.  Creatures with immunity, resistance or protection against fire effects apply these to half the damage, but not the other half.  A creature may choose spellfire for the purposes of the {i}Weapon Focus{/i} feat.\n\nUnlike most supernatural abilities, spellfire is affected by spells and magic items that affect spell-like abilities, such as a {i}rod of absorbtion{/i} or {i}rod of negation{/i} (if pointed at the manifestation rather than the wielder).  It can be thwarted or counterspelled by a {i}dispel magic{/i}, and theoretically a spellfire wielder could counterspell another&apos;s spellfire.  However, a spellfire is a supernatural ability and does not provoke an attack of opertunity when used, nor is it subject to spell resistance." compset="Special">
    <fieldval field="xSource" value="Spellfire Wielder"/>
    <usesource source="RoF"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="PickFocus"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <eval phase="First"><![CDATA[field[xSumm].text = "Deals 1d6 per level of spellfire expended. Melee or R.Touch (400ft)"]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xSplFAbsor" name="Spellfire Absorbtion" description="Absorbing spell energy\n\nA spellfire wielder can ready an action to absorb spells targeted at her as if she were a {i}rod of absorption{/i}.  She gains one level of spellfire energy for every spell level absorbed and can store a number of spellfire energy levels equal to her Constitution.  If she has reached her limit, she cannot absorb spells until she has expended some of her stored spellfire energy levels.\n\nIf an incoming spell effect has a greater number of spell levels than she can currently store, she absorbs spell levels up to her limit, and the remaining levels are divided by the orginal number of spell levels to determine what fraction of the effect gets through (as with the {i}spell turning{/i} spell, except that the caster of the spell is never at risk of being harmed).\n\nIf her Constitution decreases so that her number of stored spellfire levels is greater than her current Constitution, the excess levels discharge at a random creature in range as a destructive spellfire (see below).\n\nStored spellfire energy levels are unavailable in an {i}antimagic field{/i} but are not lost.  Once the wielder is out of the {i}antimagic field{/i} the spellfire energy levels are again available for use.  {i}Dispel Magic{/i} and other similar effects cannot negate stored spellfire energy levels.  A character with stored levels radiates magic as if he were an item with a caster level equal to the number of stored levels." compset="Special">
    <fieldval field="xSource" value="Spellfire Wielder"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="PickFocus"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <eval phase="Attr"><![CDATA[field[xSumm].text = "Absorb incoming spells as a {i}rod of absorbtion{/b}."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xSplFHeal" name="Spellfire Healing" description="Spellfire Healing\n\nA spellfire wielder can heal a target by touch, restoring 2 hit points per spellfire energy level expended for this purpose.  This is not considered positive energy, so it does not injure undead.\n\nUnlike most supernatural abilities, spellfire is affected by spells and magic items that affect spell-like abilities, such as a {i}rod of absorbtion{/i} or {i}rod of negation{/i} (if pointed at the manifestation rather than the wielder).  It can be thwarted or counterspelled by a {i}dispel magic{/i}, and theoretically a spellfire wielder could counterspell another&apos;s spellfire.  However, a spellfire is a supernatural ability and does not provoke an attack of opertunity when used, nor is it subject to spell resistance." compset="Special">
    <fieldval field="xSource" value="Spellfire Wielder"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <eval phase="PreAttr"><![CDATA[
field[xSumm].text = "Heals 2 HP per spellfire level expended."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipDoomward" name="Doomwarding" description="Doomwarding: Weapons with this ability are sometimes bestowed on adventurers favored by the church of Tymora. Typically, each is created with 7 charges. The wielder can spend 1 charge on his turn (as a free action) to make an extra attack with the weapon. She can also use 1 charge at any time, but no more than once per round, to reroll any die. The wielder can decide to spend a charge to reroll a die after learning the result of the original die roll.\n\nStrong transmutation; CL 13th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}limited wish{/i}; Price 38,500 gp; Cost 14,000 gp + 3,220 XP.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="Spend a charge to make an extra attack, once per round max.">
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="14000"/>
    <usesource source="pPGtF"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Melee"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Ranged"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Thrown"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipSplBlade" name="Spellblade" description="The wielder of a spellblade weapon is immune to a single spell chosen at the time the weapon is created. The selected spell must be one that is targeted against the wielder, not one that affects an area or creates an effect. When the wielder is next subjected to the chosen spell, the weapon absorbs it.  On his next turn, he can opt to either let the spell drain harmlessly \naway or direct it at a new target as a free action.\n\nStrong abjuration; CL 13th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}spell turning{/i}; Price 6,000 gp.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="Grants wielder immunity to selected spell, can return spell at new tar.">
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="6000"/>
    <usesource source="pPGtF"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Melee"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="CustomSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="idRodSpher" name="Rod of Spheres" description="Elminster reportedly designed the first of these rare and strange rods, but wizards all over Toril have since made many copies. The sole function of a rod of spheres is to create large, transparent bubbles, each with a radius of 3 feet. These bubbles glow softly, giving off light equivalent to that of a candle. The bubbles float along gently at a speed of 20 feet per round as directed by the wielder of the rod, and each can hold up to 140 pounds of creatures or items. Any object within a bubble is protected from exposure to the elements (rain, wind, snow, or the like, though the bubbles provide no special bonuses or resistances against energy attacks) and is affected as if by a feather fall spell should it fall more than 10 feet. The bubbles last up to 8 hours or until ruptured.\nA bubble is not a prison; any intelligent being that is not securely bound can break a bubble with ease. The rod of spheres has 50 charges when it is created, and the formation of each bubble costs 1 charge.\n\nModerate evocation [force]; CL 9th; Craft Rod, {i}feather fall{/i}, {i}Tenser&#146;s floating disk{/i}; Price 25,000 gp.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Rod" summary="Create 3ft diameter spheres that hold upto 140 lbs and have feather fall.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="117000"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="50"/>
    <usesource source="pPGtF"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Rod"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="CustCharge"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEverbrAr" name="Everbright (Armor)" description="This quality can only be applied to metal armor. The armor is as bright and shiny as polished silver. The armor never tarnishes and is immune to acid and rust attacks. The wearer gains acid resistance 5.\n\nCaster Level: 12th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, spellcaster 12th level+; Market Price: +1 bonus.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="+5 Acid Resist; Armor immune to rust and attacks.">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+1"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Armor"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Shield"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRsAcid"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[
      if (container.parent.field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
          #applyresist[xDamRsAcid, 5]
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipMagEat" name="Magic Eating" description="This type of armor is normally decorated with spirals and fanged mouths.  It functions exactly like \narmor of spell resistance with spell resistance 13, except that if the spell resistance is effective against a spell that targets only the wearer, the armor consumes the spell and gives the wearer 1d8 temporary hit points. These hit points do not stack, so it is impossible to have more than 8 temporary hit points from the armor at any time.\n\nCaster Level: 16th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}the Simbul&#146;s synostodweomer{/i}, {i}spell resistance{/i}; Market Price: +3 bonus.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="+13 SR, Grants 1d8 temp HP, non-stacking." replaces="ipMagicEat">
    <comment>Replaces Magic-Eating from the Spell Compendium.</comment>
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+3"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor" name="Armor" abbrev="Armor"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xSplRs"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[

      if (container.parent.field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
         #applysr[13]
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipProfAgTr" name="Proof against Transmutation" description="The character wearing this armor is impervious to transmutation effects that alter his or her form, including polymorph, petrification, and even disintegration.\n\nCaster Level: 12th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}spell immunity{/i}; Market Price: +6 bonus.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="Grants Immunity to transmutation effects and disintigration.">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+6"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor" name="Armor" abbrev="Armor"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xImmPoly"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xImmPetri"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[      if (container.parent.field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
         container.parent.field[hTotal].value = 1
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipNimble" name="Nimbleness" description="This type of armor feels lighter and less restrictive than other armor of its type. While the actual weight is unchanged, the maximum Dexterity bonus increases by +2 and the armor check penalty decreases by 1. \n\nCaster Level: 8th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}cat&#146;s grace{/i}; Market Price: +1 bonus.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="+2 Max Dex; -1 armor check penalty." replaces="ipNimblene">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+1"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor" name="Armor" abbrev="Armor"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="2500"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we're a armor, reduce our penalties now - we have to wait until
      ~ now to do it because our armor check penalty won't have been set until now
      if (container.parent.tagis[component.BaseArmor] <> 0) then
        container.parent.field[mMaxDex].value += 2
        container.parent.field[mArmorChk].value -= 3
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipStrenLes" name="Strength, Lesser" description="The character wearing this armor gains a +2 enhancement bonus to Strength.\nCaster Level: 12th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}bull&#146;s strength{/i}; Market Price: +2, add +8,000 gp.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="+2 Enhancement Bonus to Strength">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+2"/>
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="8000"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor" name="Armor" abbrev="Armor"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[      if (container.parent.field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
        #enhancementbonus[hero.child[aSTR], 2]
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipStrenGr" name="Strength, Greater" description="The character wearing this armor gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Strength.\n\nCaster Level: 12th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}bull&#146;s strength{/i}; Market Price: gp; +4, add +32,000 gp.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="+4 Enhancement Bonus to Strength">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+4"/>
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="32000"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor" name="Armor" abbrev="Armor"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[      if (container.parent.field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
        #enhancementbonus[hero.child[aSTR], 4]
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipRadHold" name="Radiant Holding" description="This property (sometimes employedby wizard&#146;s guards in the Old Empires) can only be placed on ranged weapon ammunition. A radiant holding projectile turns into a pulse of silvery radiance when shot. Any attack with such a projectile is a ranged touch attack. The projectile inflicts 1 point of force damage (instead of its normal damage), but the target must also make a Will save (DC 17) or be held (as the hold monster spell).\n\nCaster Level: 9th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}magic missile{/i}, {i}hold monster{/i}; Market Price: +3 bonus.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="Converts  attack to a burst of light (1 force damage) hold monster.">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+3"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Ranged"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iCormyGrSh" name="Cormyrian Greatshield" description="These +1 arrow deflection large steel shields are popular among those who hunt evil humanoids in the Storm Horns.  They are easily recognizable by the insignia of a purple dragon standing upon a broken arrow.\n\nCaster Level: 5th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}shield{/i}; Market Price: 9,170 gp; Cost to Create: 4,670 gp + 360 XP.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="MagicArmor">
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="+1"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="9170"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <child entity="mSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="mShlLtStl"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iLaerSplSh" name="Laeral&#146;s Spell Shield" description="Named for Laeral Silverhand Arunsun, who created the first shield of this type, this +1 large steel shield gives the wielder spell resistance 17 against all spells with the force descriptor.\nCaster Level: 15th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, shield, wall of force, spell resistance; Market Price: 9,170 gp; Cost to Create: 4,670 gp + 360 XP.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="MagicArmor" summary="+17 SR against spells of the force descriptor.">
