    </thing>
  <thing id="iGauntValo" name="Gauntlets of the Valorous" description="Made for the heroes of Myth Drannor, these +3 gauntlets come in many forms, from massive silvery elbow-length gauntlets to five finger-rings chained to a bracelet. Usually only one gauntlet of a pair is found.\nThey grant no bonus to Armor Class (their enhancement bonus applies only to their weapon characteristics) and do not interfere with arcane spellcasting. When both gauntlets of a matching pair are worn together, they have one of the following additional command-activated abilities, depending upon the pair:\n\n{b}Additional                            Additional{/b}\n{b}Ability                                       Prerequisite                             Market Price{/b}\nChain lightning 1/day            {i}chain lightning                            +56,000 gp\nFlame blade 2/day                 {i}flame blade                                  +38,000 gp\nHeal 1/day                                {i}heal                                               +48,000 gp\nHold monster by touch         {i}hold monster                              +30,000 gp\n1/day\nPolymorph other by touch   {i}polymorph other                        +26,000 gp\n1/day\nRegenerate 1/day                 {i}regenerate                                   +66,000 gp\nRepulsion 1/day                    {i}repulsion                                       +56,000 gp\nShocking grasp 3/day         {i}shocking grasp                           +66,000 gp\nStone to flesh or flesh to    {i}stone to flesh                              +50,000 gp\nstone (by touch) 1/day or       {i}flesh to stone\nTelekinesis (violent thrust)    {i}telekinesis                                +20,000 gp\nby touch 2/day\n\nCaster Level: 13th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, prerequisite spells; Market Price: 18,302; Cost to Create: 9,302 gp + 360 XP.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="MagicWep" summary="Gains an ability based on nature of the gauntlets.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="18302"/>
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="+3"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
