  <thing id="sClrAzuTri" name="Azuth&apos;s Exalted Triad" description="You alter one of your prepared spells so that you can cast it multiple times before it is expended.\nThe prepared spell must be of 3rd level or lower, and once the exalted triad is cast, you may cast the altered spell two additional times (a total of three times) before it is expended.\nThe altered spell functions normally and requires components or XP for each use as if you were casting three separate spells.\nIf you later choose to prepare a different spell in that spell slot, any extra castings provided by the exalted triad are lost.\nYou cannot cast exalted triad more than once upon a prepared spell.\nThis spell was created by the clerics of Azuth.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic to Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Spell">
