  <thing id="mCopper" name="Copper" description="Quite familiar to poor folk across the world, copper is known by spellcasters to be a magical purifier, aiding in magic that negates sickness and poison. While its brilliant color makes it popular for ornamental items, its relative softness makes it unsuitable for armor or weapons unless magically treated (which also activates its resistance).\nHowever, it is often used in items that provide protection from cold.\nArmor made from magically treated copper grants cold resistance 2. Items not primarily of metal are not meaningfully affected. (A suit of chainmail is affected, while a suit of studded leather is not.)\nMagically treated copper weighs the same as steel, has hardness 10, and has 30 hit points per inch of thickness.\n\n{b}Weapon Benefit:{/b} None.\n{b}Armor Benefit:{/b} Adds +2 Cold Resistance.\n{b}Market Price Modifier:{/b} Armor +2,000 gp.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Material" summary="+2 Cold resist.">
    <fieldval field="eMatCost" value="2000"/>
    <usesource source="MagFaerun"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatArmOK"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatShldOK"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatRqMetal"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatWepOK"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatForceMs"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MastCstInc"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRsCold"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[      var result as number
      ~ Set damage resistance to Cold
      var damage as number
          damage = 2

      ~ Add to our custom description if we're armor
      if (container.parent.tagis[component.BaseArmor] <> 0) then
~        #applyresist[xDamRsCold, damage]
         field[eMatDesc].text &= " Adds +2 Cold Resist."
      else
        done
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="mDarksteel" name="Darksteel" description="Darksteel is silvery in hue when polished or cut, but its exposed surfaces have a deep, gleaming purple luster. The process for making this type of steel was once lost, but has been recently rediscovered thanks to some ancient dwarven texts. The alloy is made from meteoric iron tempered with a variety of special oils.\nArmor made from darksteel grants acid resistance 2.\nWeapons forged of darksteel inflict +1 point of electricity damage each time they hit (this is cumulative with other abilities, such as shock or shocking burst). Items not primarily of metal are not meaningfully affected. (A longsword or a suit of chainmail is affected, while a spear or a suit of studded leather is not.)\nDarksteel weighs the same as steel, has hardness 10, and has 30 hit points per inch of thickness.\n\n{b}Weapon Benefit:{/b} +1 Electricity damage, (stacks with {i}shocking{/i} and {i}shocking burst{/i})\n{b}Armor Benefit:{/b} Adds +2 Acid Resistance\n{b}Market Price Modifier:{/b} Armor +2,000 gp; Weapon +1,500 gp.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Material" summary="+2 Acid Resist to weapons, +1 Electric damage for weapons, (stacks).">
