    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[      var result as number
      ~ Set damage resistance to Acid
      var damage as number
          damage = 2

      ~ Add to our custom description if we're armor
      if (container.parent.tagis[component.BaseArmor] <> 0) then
~        #applyresist[xDamRsCold, damage]
         field[eMatDesc].text &= " Adds +2 Acid Resist."
      else
         field[eMatDesc].text &= " Adds +1 Electric per hit."
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="mFeverIron" name="Fever Iron" description="In some volcanic craters, pools of molten metal collect and are never allowed to fully cool. Sometimes these pools of semisolid metal attract the raw energy of the Weave and are transformed into what the dwarves call fever iron. Fever iron can be made fully solid through a magical process that includes application of intense cold, after which it can be worked like \nnormal iron.\n\nArmor made from fever iron grants fire resistance 2.\nWeapons forged of fever iron inflict +1 point of fire damage each time they hit (this is cumulative with other abilities, such as flaming or flaming burst). Items not primarily of metal are not meaningfully affected. (A longsword or a suit of chainmail is affected, while a spear or a suit of studded leather is not.) Fever iron can never be used in a magic item that uses cold effects, such as a frost or icy burst weapon.\nFever iron weighs the same as steel, has hardness 12, and has 30 hit points per inch of thickness.\n\n{b}Weapon Benefit:{/b} +1 Fire damage, (stacks with {i}flaming{/i} and {i}flaming burst{/i})\n{b}Armor Benefit:{/b} Adds +2 Fire Resistance.\n{b}Market Price Modifier:{/b} Armor +2,000 gp; Weapon +1,500 gp.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Magic of Faer&#251;n{/i}, 3.0 Edition" compset="Material" summary="+2 Fire Resist to weapons, +1 Fire damage for weapons, (stacks).">
